                  beta(+)-activity distributions is desirable. An
                  established and general purpose radiation transport
                  code is preferred. FLUKA is a candidate for such a
                  code. For application to in-beam PET therapy
                  monitoring, the code has to model with high accuracy
                  both the electromagnetic and nuclear interactions
                  responsible for dose deposition and beta(+)-activity
                  production, respectively. In this work, the
                  electromagnetic interaction in FLUKA was adjusted to
                  reproduce the same pArticle range as from the
                  experimentally validated treatment planning software
